  "title": "Audio Visual Technician",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities (Includes but not limited to):</strong></p><ul><li>Handles and manage setup of AV equipment e.g. LED wall screen, lightings system, LED projectors, sound system and others.</li><li>Perform routine AV System checking.</li><li>Set up and operate AV system for events and daily operation.</li><li>Logistics set up for all operations of AV equipment for event.</li><li>Ensuring smooth performance through prompt troubleshooting of technical issues.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as and when assigned e.g. Rehearsal and AV Test. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>GCE ‘N/O’ Level or NTC/ITE Grade 2/3 in Electrical / Air Conditioning / Building Services / M&E engineering</li><li>Preferably 2 to 3 years' experience in electrical, air conditioning, building services or M&E engineering maintenance works, preferably in Club/Hotel industry</li><li>Good communication skills</li><li>Able to work shifts, weekends, and overtime </li></ul>",
